# .gitattributes tells Git how to treat specific paths — here it enforces
# consistent line endings and correct text/binary handling across environments.
# Without it, contributors on Windows (CRLF) and macOS/Linux (LF) would
# produce noisy, platform-dependent diffs and risk corrupting binary files.

# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository; working-tree line
# endings follow each contributor's platform defaults.
* text=auto

# Never touch binary assets.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.ico binary
*.woff2 binary
